{"author":{"id":"1949ffc23f11a8cb4f8c42a45c9ad241b49570df9a18687489e9ea78d87c54a3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772565662,"nonce":"47FHCywR6hvZSXX+r7sA6h3u87c=","title":"Phase 6: Wire Studio training backend to real JAX training","message":"The Studio training worker (feedbax/web/worker/app.py) is currently a stub that runs fake\n0.98^batch loss decay with no actual JAX computation. The graph spec sent from the frontend\nis ignored entirely. Phase 6 replaces this with real training.\n\n## What needs to happen\n\n1. **Graph spec → model instantiation**: The worker receives a graph spec (list of nodes,\n   edges, component types, params). It needs to instantiate the corresponding feedbax\n   model objects (plant, controller, loss terms) from this spec.\n\n2. **Training loop**: Run actual JAX/equinox training using the instantiated model.\n   Stream real metrics (loss, gradient norms, per-term losses) back via SSE events.\n\n3. **Trajectory snapshots**: Periodically run eval episodes and stream trajectory data\n   back so the 3D viewer shows real arm movements.\n\n4. **Weight checkpoints**: Serialize trained weights and make them available via the\n   checkpoint endpoint.\n\n## Proposed minimal implementation (config-driven bridge)\n\nRather than a full graph-spec interpreter, implement a config-driven bridge:\n- The frontend sends a structured TrainingConfig (network_type, hidden_dim, plant_type,\n  loss weights, optimizer config, n_batches, etc.) alongside the graph spec\n- The worker maps this config to a known training entry point\n  (e.g. bbooddyy's train_oracles_supervised.py or feedbax's own training infrastructure)\n- This avoids building a full graph compiler while still getting real training\n\n## Full implementation (graph interpreter)\n\nLong-term: a graph compiler that walks the ComponentSpec tree, instantiates feedbax\nComponent objects for each node, wires them according to edges, and runs training.\nThis requires a registry mapping component type names to Python classes and a\nconnection mapping from port names to feedbax's wire/carry semantics.\n\n## Files to touch\n\n- feedbax/web/worker/app.py — replace _run_training() stub\n- feedbax/web/api/models/training.py — extend TrainingRequest with config fields\n- feedbax/web/api/routes/training.py — pass config through to worker\n- feedbax/web/frontend/src/... — send config from Training panel\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- Starting training in Studio runs real JAX gradient updates\n- Loss curve in the Training tab shows real decreasing loss\n- 3D viewer shows real arm trajectories from eval rollouts\n- Checkpoint download returns real serialized weights","files":null}]}